main event: Observation of an unusual object in the sky over Budd Lake, New Jersey, on May 6th.
interesting points: The observation included both ground-radar and visual types,The object was determined to possibly be a balloon or aircraft,The document is part of the Project Blue Book investigation program,The report also refers to a letter sent to the President regarding the sighting,There were previous observations reported on May 23rd and 24th that were identified as the ECHO-II satellite.
